According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Asia-Pacific avocado oil market was valued at USD 42.8 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 47.3 million in 2025 to USD 78.9 million by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.8% during the forecast period. Rising consumer awareness of healthy dietary choices, increasing disposable incomes, expanding e-commerce platforms, and the growing popularity of premium natural ingredients in both food and cosmetic applications are driving market expansion across the region.
Avocado oil has emerged as a premium edible oil due to its high smoke point, rich content of monounsaturated fats, antioxidants, and essential vitamins. It is increasingly being adopted in home cooking, gourmet foodservice, and health-focused diets while also gaining popularity as an ingredient in skincare, haircare, and cosmetic products because of its moisturizing and regenerative properties.
