The report highlights that rapid urbanization, Western dietary influences, and the growing preference for clean-label and functional foods are fueling demand across countries such as Australia, New Zealand, China, India, Japan, South Korea, and Southeast Asian nations. Online retail channels have significantly improved product accessibility, enabling premium international and regional brands to reach a wider customer base.
Despite strong growth prospects, the market continues to face challenges including premium pricing compared to conventional edible oils, supply chain volatility due to fluctuating avocado harvests, and limited consumer awareness in several developing markets. Product authenticity concerns and competition from traditional cooking oils such as palm, sesame, coconut, and groundnut oils also remain key industry challenges.
The report identifies significant opportunities in localized avocado cultivation, product innovation including flavored and spray-format oils, and the rapid expansion of natural and organic personal care products. Manufacturers are also expected to benefit from strategic partnerships with global avocado-producing countries to ensure stable supply while expanding their presence across high-growth Asia-Pacific markets.
Australasia remains the leading regional market owing to strong domestic production, advanced agricultural infrastructure, and a mature health-conscious consumer base. Meanwhile, East Asia and Southeast Asia are expected to witness rapid growth, supported by rising disposable incomes, increasing digital retail penetration, and growing demand for premium wellness products.
